298real_T rt_atan2d_snf(real_T u0, real_T u1)

          
299{

          
300  real_T y;

          
301  if (std::isnan(u0) || std::isnan(u1)) {

          
302    y = (rtNaN);

          
303  } else if (std::isinf(u0) && std::isinf(u1)) {

          
304    int32_T u0_0;

          
305    int32_T u1_0;

          
306    if (u0 > 0.0) {

          
307      u0_0 = 1;

          
308    } else {

          
309      u0_0 = -1;

          
310    }

          
311

          
312    if (u1 > 0.0) {

          
313      u1_0 = 1;

          
314    } else {

          
315      u1_0 = -1;

          
316    }

          
317

          
318    y = std::atan2(static_cast<real_T>(u0_0), static_cast<real_T>(u1_0));

          
319  } else if (u1 == 0.0) {

          
320    if (u0 > 0.0) {

          
321      y = RT_PI / 2.0;

          
322    } else if (u0 < 0.0) {

          
323      y = -(RT_PI / 2.0);

          
324    } else {

          
325      y = 0.0;

          
326    }

          
327  } else {

          
328    y = std::atan2(u0, u1);

          
329  }

          
330

          
331  return y;

          
332}

334// Function for MATLAB Function: '<S20>/vehicle model'

          
335void ReqsGroundTruthModelClass::ReqsGround_automlvehdynftiresat(real_T Ftire_x,

          
336  real_T Ftire_y, real_T b_Fxtire_sat, real_T b_Fytire_sat, real_T *Ftire_xs,

          
337  real_T *Ftire_ys)

          
338{

          
339  real_T Ftire_mag;

          
340  real_T Ftire_x_max;

          
341  real_T Ftire_y_max;

          
342  real_T theta_Ftire;

          
343  theta_Ftire = rt_atan2d_snf(Ftire_x, Ftire_y);

          
344  Ftire_y_max = std::cos(theta_Ftire);

          
345  Ftire_x_max = b_Fxtire_sat * Ftire_y_max;

          
346  theta_Ftire = std::sin(theta_Ftire);

          
347  Ftire_mag = b_Fytire_sat * theta_Ftire;

          
348  Ftire_mag = b_Fxtire_sat * b_Fytire_sat / std::sqrt(Ftire_x_max * Ftire_x_max

          
349    + Ftire_mag * Ftire_mag);

          
350  Ftire_x_max = Ftire_mag * theta_Ftire;

          
351  Ftire_y_max *= Ftire_mag;

          
352  *Ftire_xs = Ftire_x;

          
353  if (std::abs(Ftire_x) > std::abs(Ftire_x_max)) {

          
354    *Ftire_xs = Ftire_x_max;

          
355  }

          
356

          
357  *Ftire_ys = Ftire_y;

          
358  if (std::abs(Ftire_y) > std::abs(Ftire_y_max)) {

          
359    *Ftire_ys = Ftire_y_max;

          
360  }

          
361}

363void ReqsGroundTruthModelClass::ReqsGroundTruth_mean(const real_T x_data[],

          
364  const int32_T x_size[2], real_T y[3])

          
365{

          
366  int32_T vlen;

          
367  vlen = x_size[0];

          
368  if (x_size[0] == 0) {

          
369    y[0] = 0.0;

          
370    y[1] = 0.0;

          
371    y[2] = 0.0;

          
372  } else {

          
373    for (int32_T b_xi{0}; b_xi < 3; b_xi++) {

          
374      int32_T xpageoffset;

          
375      xpageoffset = b_xi * x_size[0];

          
376      y[b_xi] = x_data[xpageoffset];

          
377      for (int32_T k{2}; k <= vlen; k++) {

          
378        y[b_xi] += x_data[(xpageoffset + k) - 1];

          
379      }

          
380    }

          
381  }

          
382

          
383  y[0] /= static_cast<real_T>(x_size[0]);

          
384  y[1] /= static_cast<real_T>(x_size[0]);

          
385  y[2] /= static_cast<real_T>(x_size[0]);

          
386}

          
387

          
388real_T ReqsGroundTruthModelClass::ReqsGroundTruth_norm(const real_T x[3])

          
389{

          
390  real_T absxk;

          
391  real_T scale;

          
392  real_T t;

          
393  real_T y;

          
394  scale = 3.3121686421112381E-170;

          
395  absxk = std::abs(x[0]);

          
396  if (absxk > 3.3121686421112381E-170) {

          
397    y = 1.0;

          
398    scale = absxk;

          
399  } else {

          
400    t = absxk / 3.3121686421112381E-170;

          
401    y = t * t;

          
402  }

          
403

          
404  absxk = std::abs(x[1]);

          
405  if (absxk > scale) {

          
406    t = scale / absxk;

          
407    y = y * t * t + 1.0;

          
408    scale = absxk;

          
409  } else {

          
410    t = absxk / scale;

          
411    y += t * t;

          
412  }

          
413

          
414  absxk = std::abs(x[2]);

          
415  if (absxk > scale) {

          
416    t = scale / absxk;

          
417    y = y * t * t + 1.0;

          
418    scale = absxk;

          
419  } else {

          
420    t = absxk / scale;

          
421    y += t * t;

          
422  }

          
423

          
424  return scale * std::sqrt(y);

          
425}

806  }

          
807

          
808  pAutoOrientCache->Roll = *b_egoVehicle_Roll;

          
809  if ((R_idx_0 == 0.0) && (R_idx_1 == 0.0)) {

          
810    *b_egoVehicle_Pitch = 90.0;

          
811  } else {

          
812    *b_egoVehicle_Pitch = rt_atan2d_snf(-(b_y1_0[0] * centroid[1] - centroid[0] *

          
813      b_y1_0[1]), std::sqrt(R_idx_0 * R_idx_0 + R_idx_1 * R_idx_1)) *

          
814      57.295779513082323;

          
815  }

          
816

          
817  pAutoOrientCache->Pitch = *b_egoVehicle_Pitch;

          
818}

1096boolean_T ReqsGroundTruthModelClass::ReqsGroundTruth_vectorAny(const boolean_T

          
1097  x_data[], const int32_T x_size[2])

          
1098{

          
1099  int32_T b_k;

          
1100  boolean_T exitg1;

          
1101  boolean_T y;

          
1102  y = false;

          
1103  b_k = 0;

          
1104  exitg1 = false;

          
1105  while ((!exitg1) && (b_k <= x_size[1] - 1)) {

          
1106    if (x_data[b_k]) {

          
1107      y = true;

          
1108      exitg1 = true;

          
1109    } else {

          
1110      b_k++;

          
1111    }

          
1112  }

          
1113

          
1114  return y;

          
1115}

          
1116

          
1117void ReqsGroundTruthModelClass::ReqsGr_genrand_uint32_vector_km(uint32_T mt[625],

          
1118  uint32_T u[2])

          
1119{

          
1120  for (int32_T b_j{0}; b_j < 2; b_j++) {

          
1121    uint32_T mti;

          
1122    uint32_T y;

          
1123    mti = mt[624] + 1U;

          
1124    if (mt[624] + 1U >= 625U) {

          
1125      int32_T b_kk;

          
1126      for (b_kk = 0; b_kk < 227; b_kk++) {

          
1127        y = (mt[b_kk + 1] & 2147483647U) | (mt[b_kk] & 2147483648U);

          
1128        if ((y & 1U) == 0U) {

          
1129          y >>= 1U;

          
1130        } else {

          
1131          y = y >> 1U ^ 2567483615U;

          
1132        }

          
1133

          
1134        mt[b_kk] = mt[b_kk + 397] ^ y;

          
1135      }

          
1136

          
1137      for (b_kk = 0; b_kk < 396; b_kk++) {

          
1138        y = (mt[b_kk + 227] & 2147483648U) | (mt[b_kk + 228] & 2147483647U);

          
1139        if ((y & 1U) == 0U) {

          
1140          y >>= 1U;

          
1141        } else {

          
1142          y = y >> 1U ^ 2567483615U;

          
1143        }

          
1144

          
1145        mt[b_kk + 227] = mt[b_kk] ^ y;

          
1146      }

          
1147

          
1148      y = (mt[623] & 2147483648U) | (mt[0] & 2147483647U);

          
1149      if ((y & 1U) == 0U) {

          
1150        y >>= 1U;

          
1151      } else {

          
1152        y = y >> 1U ^ 2567483615U;

          
1153      }

          
1154

          
1155      mt[623] = mt[396] ^ y;

          
1156      mti = 1U;

          
1157    }

          
1158

          
1159    y = mt[static_cast<int32_T>(mti) - 1];

          
1160    mt[624] = mti;

          
1161    y ^= y >> 11U;

          
1162    y ^= y << 7U & 2636928640U;

          
1163    y ^= y << 15U & 4022730752U;

          
1164    u[b_j] = y >> 18U ^ y;

          
1165  }

          
1166}

          
1167

          
1168real_T ReqsGroundTruthModelClass::ReqsGroundTruth_genrandu_km(uint32_T mt[625])

          
1169{

          
1170  real_T r;

          
1171  uint32_T b_u[2];

          
1172

          
1173  // ========================= COPYRIGHT NOTICE ============================

          
1174  //  This is a uniform (0,1) pseudorandom number generator based on:

          
1175  //

          
1176  //  A C-program for MT19937, with initialization improved 2002/1/26.

          
1177  //  Coded by Takuji Nishimura and Makoto Matsumoto.

1211  int32_T exitg1;

          
1212  do {

          
1213    exitg1 = 0;

          
1214    ReqsGr_genrand_uint32_vector_km(mt, b_u);

          
1215    r = (static_cast<real_T>(b_u[0] >> 5U) * 6.7108864E+7 + static_cast<real_T>

          
1216         (b_u[1] >> 6U)) * 1.1102230246251565E-16;

          
1217    if (r == 0.0) {

          
1218      int32_T k;

          
1219      boolean_T b_isvalid;

          
1220      if ((mt[624] >= 1U) && (mt[624] < 625U)) {

          
1221        b_isvalid = true;

          
1222      } else {

          
1223        b_isvalid = false;

          
1224      }

          
1225

          
1226      if (b_isvalid) {

          
1227        boolean_T exitg2;

          
1228        b_isvalid = false;

          
1229        k = 0;

          
1230        exitg2 = false;

          
1231        while ((!exitg2) && (k + 1 < 625)) {

          
1232          if (mt[k] == 0U) {

          
1233            k++;

          
1234          } else {

          
1235            b_isvalid = true;

          
1236            exitg2 = true;

          
1237          }

          
1238        }

          
1239      }

          
1240

          
1241      if (!b_isvalid) {

          
1242        uint32_T r_0;

          
1243        r_0 = 67U;

          
1244        mt[0] = 67U;

          
1245        for (k = 0; k < 623; k++) {

          
1246          r_0 = ((r_0 >> 30U ^ r_0) * 1812433253U + k) + 1U;

          
1247          mt[k + 1] = r_0;

          
1248        }

          
1249

          
1250        mt[624] = 624U;

          
1251      }

          
1252    } else {

          
1253      exitg1 = 1;

          
1254    }

          
1255  } while (exitg1 == 0);

          
1256

          
1257  return r;

          
1258}

          
1259

          
1260void ReqsGroundTruthModelClass::ReqsGroundTruth_filter(real_T b, real_T a[2],

          
1261  const real_T x[3], const real_T zi[3], real_T y[3], real_T zf[3])

          
1262{

          
1263  if ((!std::isinf(a[0])) && (!std::isnan(a[0])) && (!(a[0] == 0.0)) && (a[0] !=

          
1264       1.0)) {

          
1265    b /= a[0];

          
1266    a[1] /= a[0];

          
1267  }

          
1268

          
1269  y[0] = x[0] * b + zi[0];

          
1270  zf[0] = -y[0] * a[1];

          
1271  y[1] = x[1] * b + zi[1];

          
1272  zf[1] = -y[1] * a[1];

          
1273  y[2] = x[2] * b + zi[2];

          
1274  zf[2] = -y[2] * a[1];

          
1275}

          
1276

          
1277void ReqsGroundTruthModelClass::ReqsGroundTru_SystemCore_step_k

          
1278  (g_fusion_internal_Acceleromet_T *obj, const real_T varargin_1[3], const
